org.parboiled.matchers
Interface Matcher<V>

Type Parameters:
V - the type of the value field of a parse tree node
All Superinterfaces:
GraphNode<Matcher<V>>, Rule
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractMatcher, ActionMatcher, AnyMatcher, CharIgnoreCaseMatcher, CharMatcher, CharRangeMatcher, CharSetMatcher, CustomMatcher, EmptyMatcher, FirstOfMatcher, OneOrMoreMatcher, OptionalMatcher, ProxyMatcher, SequenceMatcher, TestMatcher, TestNotMatcher, VarFramingMatcher, ZeroOrMoreMatcher
public interface Matcher<V>
extends Rule, GraphNode<Matcher<V>>

A Matcher instance is responsible for "executing" a specific Rule instance, i.e. it implements the actual rule type specific matching logic. Since it extends the GraphNode interface it can have submatchers.
